OL,3,CMother calls for safety improvements
OL,4,Cafter son hit by train at crossing
OL,6,FHarry's mother, Leanne Golding, said
OL,7,F"It was the worst feeling ever. Harry
OL,8,Fwas my only son and my absolute world."
OL,10,F"It's something I will never get over.
OL,11,FJust that split second mistake and
OL,12,FHarry's paid the ultimate price for
OL,13,Fit."
OL,15,FHarry's family say they may never know
OL,16,Fexactly what happened that morning but
OL,17,Fthey believe the level crossing near
OL,18,Ftheir home is unsafe, as it has no
OL,19,Flights, CCTV or any way of warning
OL,20,Fpedestrians of oncoming trains.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/6
